title: Tremblay, Dewitt Lead Locals at State Golf
text:
Tremblay, Dewitt Lead Locals at State Golf 
By Zach Schneider October 12, 2015 Updated Oct 12, 2015 at 8:19 PM CDT 
Madison, WI (NNCNOW.com) --- Hayward's Lauren Tremblay and Spooner's Dani Dewitt are the top local players after day one at the WIAA Division 2 girls' golf tournament, which is being played at University Ridge in Madison, Wis. 
Tremblay fired a 13-over-par 85 to finish day one in 12th place, while Dewitt shot a 15-over-par 87 to sit in 14th place. 
Hayward is in fourth place as a team after the first of two rounds, 30 shots off the lead, while Spooner is in fifth place and 36 shots back. 
Day two of the WIAA girls' golf tournament is scheduled for Tuesday morning.
